//The Jailors tossed away their keys and set their wards free//

//When the brass played.//

//The Bookburners extinguished their lights and left without a fight//

//When the brass played.//

//The Brokers melted down their coins, estranged loved ones they joined//

//When the brass played.//

//The Mekhanites wound their springs down, their connection with WAN redound//

//When the brass played.//

//Frequencies switched off, Vikander-Kneed and Westhead blown away by the quaff//

//When the brass played.//

//The Watchers left their site, no longer caring about being proven right//

//When the brass played.//

//The Pugilists put down their gloves, their pointless crusade away they shoved//

//When the brass played.//

//The Librarians closed their books, to the next adventure they looked//

//When the brass played.//

//The Circus gave a last bow to their biggest crowd//

//When the brass played.//

//The Evasive Man tipped his hat, and that was that//

//When the brass played.//

//The **##green|Fae##** left their **##blue|forest##**, an ancient song of peace chorused//

//When the brass played.//

//The Queen declared checkmate, not a second too late//

//When the brass played.//

//The Zookeeper's life work complete, they drifted off to sleep//

//When the brass played.//

//And no one gave a fuss, when the world turned to rust//

//because [https://scp-wiki.wikidot.com/scp-6999 the brass played].//

